Hyundai Signs Deal to Feature on Piccadilly Lights, FT Reports

-- B y   R a c h e l   G r a h a m
-- 
2011-06-04T09:31:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-04/hyundai-signs-deal-to-feature-on-piccadilly-lights-ft-reports.html
Hyundai Motor Co. (005380)  signed a deal to
advertise on the  Piccadilly Lights  advertising space in central
 London  owned by  Land Securities Group Plc (LAND) , the Financial Times
reported, without saying where it got the information.  The agreement, which will see Hyundai replace Sanyo
Electric Co., is worth about 2 million pounds ($3.3 million) a
year, the report said. The advertising site is seen by more than
34 million people a year, according to the FT.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rachel Graham in London at 
 rgraham13@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dick Schumacher at 
 dschumacher@bloomberg.net  